metadata.name: Night Moves Series: "Lonesome"
metadata.description:
There are nights in New York City where taking a walk alone feels like a dream. Nights when the snow falls so slowly and the lights are so faint, that it makes everything look like a slow motion clip of a movie. Those nights when you look around and get lost in thought. A magical feeling that makes you realize that nothing else matters but here and now. A flash that in a split of a second makes you forget you were lonesome moments ago. These nights don’t happen often but when they do, they stick around in your mind forever. 

Sony A1
G Master 50mm 1.2
ISO 800
